## Backtest vs Live Gap Analysis
```python
# Run monthly to check if live results match backtest predictions
ACCEPTABLE_GAP = {
    "win_rate":   0.05,   # Live win rate within ±5pp of backtest
    "sharpe":     0.30,   # Live Sharpe within 30% of backtest
    "trade_freq": 0.30,   # Live trade frequency within 30% of backtest
}

def analyze_backtest_live_gap(backtest_stats: dict, live_stats: dict) -> dict:
    gaps = {}
    for metric, threshold in ACCEPTABLE_GAP.items():
        bt_val   = backtest_stats[metric]
        live_val = live_stats[metric]
        gap      = abs(bt_val - live_val) / bt_val
        gaps[metric] = {
            "backtest":    bt_val,
            "live":        live_val,
            "gap_pct":     gap,
            "within_tolerance": gap <= threshold,
            "status": "OK" if gap <= threshold else "INVESTIGATE",
        }
    return gaps
```

## Guardrails
- Paper trading must run for minimum 4 weeks before any live deployment
- Regression suite must pass 100% before any deployment — no skipping failing tests
- Fill model must be calibrated against real Kalshi fill data quarterly
- Any backtest-vs-live gap > acceptable thresholds triggers a mandatory QR + QD review
- Never adjust the fill model to make paper results look better — it must reflect reality
